    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Despite multiple credibility factor gaps at MRL 5, the assessment team accepted the package on the basis that the primary hemolysis validation result demonstrates NIH predictions within 12% of experimental values across all five operating points, and the 95th-percentile Monte Carlo NIH value (0.0102 g/100 L) remains substantially below the clinical threshold (0.025 g/100 L). The detailed technical narrative in the primary validation result (TR-VAD-2025-07) was considered to provide sufficient audit trail for the simulation campaign. Residual gaps in model-form uncertainty, test sample variability, and input equivalency traceability are acknowledged as limitations to be addressed in a subsequent MRL 5 reassessment.",
